BELOW BEFORE APPLYING.   APPLY TO BE A PEER TUTOR         Eligibility:  Applicants must be  undergraduates able to say YES to all of the below.    YES/NO: I have completed 104 or higher at UIC with a grade of B or above: French, German, Italian, Spanish only.  YES/NO: I can take French 296, which meets every WEDNESDAY 12-12:50, and tutor for 3 hours/week during the second half of the semester. French 296 is a 1-credit class. Contact your department to see if it can count toward a major or not.  YES/NO: I can take a class in the language that I am tutoring during the semesters I tutor.       Questions?  Contact us          Peer Tutoring    Back to main content           What is Peer Tutoring?    Meet Our Tutors     Spanish Tutors    French Tutors    Italian Tutors    German Tutors      Tutoring Schedule (ONLINE as of 3/16)     French Tutoring Schedule    German Tutoring Schedule    Italian Tutoring Schedule    Spanish Tutoring Schedule      For Students (Tips and Resources)     Writing Resources    Reading Resources    Listening Resources    Exam Resources      Become a Tutor     Peer Tutoring Application      Peer Tutoring Blog    Tutoring FAQ    Contact Peer Tutoring             Meet Our Peer Tutors  Learn more about our peer tutors in French, German, Italian, and Spanish!      For Students  Click here for tips and resources to enhance your language learning experience!      Contact Us  Do you want to schedule an event in the Language Oasis? Do you need help with a technology tool or want to schedule a workshop? Contact us with any questions you may have!                  UIC Logo         Language  And Culture  Learning Center  College of  Liberal Arts  And  Sciences         Contact   Language and Culture Learning Center  703 South Morgan St., 301 GH Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 996 2119  lclc@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    Twitter    Instagram    YouTube            UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Dis